==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Hogframe
<hw>Hog"frame`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Steam
Vessels)</fld> <def>A trussed frame extending fore and aft, usually
above deck, and intended to increase the longitudinal strength and
stiffness. Used chiefly in American river and lake steamers. Called also
<altname>hogging frame</altname>, and
<altname>hogback</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Hogged</ent>⟦br⟧
